#: Game
msgid "[Game] CaptionLong"
msgstr ""
"This game illustrates theorem proving in Lean using various topics from the "
"first year of a typical bachelor's degree programme in mathematics."

#: Game
msgid "[Game] CaptionShort"
msgstr "Explore a different universe with your smart-elf Scribble!"

#: Game
msgid "[Game] Conclusion"
msgstr "QED"

#: Game
msgid "[Game] Info"
msgstr ""
"## Project ADAM \n"
"\n"
"This educational game was developed as part of the project [ADAM: "
"Anticipating the Digital Age of Mathematics](https://hhu-adam.github.io/) "
"project at Heinrich Heine University D√ľsseldorf, funded by the *Freiraum "
"2022* programme of the *Stiftung Innovation in der Hochschullehre*.\n"
"Ongoing maintenance and development are generously supported by *Renaissance "
"Philanthropy* through the *AI for Math Fund*.\n"
"\n"
"## Game content\n"
"\n"
"**Spoiler alert** You can find an overview of the rough mathematical content "
"of all planets on [Github](https://github.com/hhu-adam/Robo?tab=readme-ov-"
"file#overview-over-existing-content).\n"
"\n"
"## Credits\n"
"\n"
"* **Project management:** Marcus Zibrowius, Immi Halupczok\n"
"* **Game engine:** Jon Eugster, Alexander Bentkamp, Patrick Massot ‚Äď see "
"[lean4game](https://github.com/leanprover-community/lean4game?tab=readme-ov-"
"file#credits)\n"
"* **Levels:** Jon Eugster, Marcus Zibrowius, Sina Hazratpour\n"
"* **Concept & Story:** Marcus Zibrowius\n"
"* **Illustrations:** [DuŇ°an Pavlińá](https://www.behance.net/dusanpavlic#)\n"
"\n"
"## Contact\n"
"\n"
"The game is constantly being revised.\n"
"We welcome your feedback, suggestions, and criticism,\n"
"for example, by email to\n"
"[Marcus Zibrowius](https://www.math.uni-duesseldorf.de/~zibrowius/).\n"
"You are equally welcome create issue's on GitHub, be it for typos, bugs or "
"feature requests:\n"
"\n"
"* Please submit issues regarding game content to the repository [Robo]"
"(https://github.com/hhu-adam/Robo/issues).\n"
"* Please submit issues regarding the server and our software to the "
"[lean4game repository](https://github.com/leanprover-community/lean4game/"
"issues)."

#: Game
msgid "[Game] Introduction"
msgstr ""
"# Game Over or QED? \n"
"\n"
"Are you curious what computer-assisted theorem proving feels like compared "
"to pen-and-paper mathematics? Then you've come to the right place! In this "
"game, you will learn how to work with the proof assistant Lean 4 and the "
"proof library mathlib.\n"
"You will verify sum formulas by induction, show that a map is surjective if "
"and only if it has a right inverse, prove that there are uncountably many "
"sequences of natural numbers, and characterise the trace as a map among all "
"functions defined on the space of square matrices.\n"
"\n"
"The interface is somewhat simplified, but if you activate *editor mode*, it "
"feels almost like VSCode, the standard IDE for Lean.\n"
"On a smartphone or tablet, it is better to stay in the default *typewriter "
"mode* and turn off all autocompletion/autocorrection features of your on-"
"screen keyboard (a.k.a. ‚Äúsmart typing‚ÄĚ, ‚Äútext recognition‚ÄĚ, ‚Äúpredictive "
"text‚ÄĚ etc.). \n"
"\n"
"Click on the first planet *Logo* to start your journey.\n"
"\n"
"## Progress\n"
"\n"
"Your game progress is stored locally in your browser as *site data*. You can "
"also download your progress via the menu and save it to your disk. Note that "
"many browsers delete *site data* and *cookies* together. \n"
"\n"
"## Rules \n"
"\n"
"If you want to take the game seriously, keep the default setting *Rules: "
"regular*.\n"
"If you just want to poke around, select *Rules: relaxed*.  This will allow "
"you to access every level immediately, even if you haven't solved the "
"previous levels yet.\n"
"\n"
"## News \n"
"\n"
"`[2026-03-20]` The game is now available in English.  If you are interested "
"in contributing translations to other languages, [please get in touch]"
"(https://github.com/hhu-adam/Robo/tree/main?tab=readme-ov-"
"file#translations)!\n"
"\n"
"For background information and credits, see *Game Info* in the menu."

