"and only if* ¬ß2 is true. \n"
"\n"
"## ¬ß3 as goal\n"
"\n"
"One way to prove ¬ß4 is to call ¬ß5 and then prove ¬ß6 and ¬ß7 separately.\n"
"\n"
"## ¬ß8 as assumption \n"
"\n"
"You can use ¬ß10 to break down an assumption of the form ¬ß9 into its two "
"components ¬ß11 and ¬ß12. Alternatively, you can also refer to these "
"components directly using ¬ß13 and ¬ß14 (where ¬ß15 abbreviates ‚Äúmodus ponens‚ÄĚ)."

