"¬ß5\n"
"extracts ¬ß6\n"
"a mapping ¬ß7 and the assumption ¬ß8.\n"
"\n"
"(Here, ¬ß9 is a predicate that depends on two variables ¬ß10 and ¬ß11.)"
msgstr ""
"You can split an assumption of the form \n"
"¬ß0\n"
"into its components ¬ß2 and ¬ß3 using ¬ß1.\n"
"\n"
"More generally, you can use ¬ß4 to invoke the axiom of choice. Suppose you "
"have an assumption of the following form: \n"
"\n"
"¬ß5\n"
"\n"
"From this assumption, ¬ß6 will extract a map ¬ß7 satisfying the assumption "
"¬ß8. \n"
"\n"
"(Here, ¬ß9 is a predicate that depends on two variables ¬ß10 and ¬ß11.)"

#. ¬ß0: `‚ąÉx, P x`
