#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"If you have given an equation ¬ß0 or an equivalence ¬ß1 as an assumption or "
"lemma,\n"
"you can use ¬ß2 to replace all occurrences of ¬ß3 in the proof target with "
"¬ß4.\n"
"\n"
"## Variants\n"
"\n"
"* ¬ß5 applies ¬ß6 backwards, i.e., replaces all ¬ß7 with ¬ß8.\n"
"* ¬ß9 applies ¬ß10, ¬ß11, and (backwards) ¬ß12.\n"
"* ¬ß13 performs the replacements in the assumption ¬ß14, not in the proof "
"target\n"
"* ¬ß15: If ¬ß16 has arguments, e.g., ¬ß17 in\n"
"¬ß18\n"
"   or in\n"
"¬ß19\n"
"   ¬ß20 searches the proof target from left to right for a matching "
"expression,\n"
"   and then replaces *all* occurrences of *the first* expression that the "
"tactic finds.\n"
"   With ¬ß21, you can replace all occurrences of the ¬ß22th expression "
"instead.\n"
"\n"
"  | before    | tactic       | after        |\n"
"  |:----------------- |:------------- - |:----------------- |\n"
"  | ¬ß23 | ¬ß24       | ¬ß25 |\n"
"  |                   | ¬ß26 | ¬ß27 |"
msgstr ""
"Given an equation ¬ß0 or an equivalence ¬ß1 as an assumption or lemma, ¬ß2 "
"replaces all occurrences of ¬ß3 in the goal with ¬ß4. \n"
"\n"
"## Variants \n"
"\n"
"* ¬ß5 applies ¬ß6 backwards, i.e. replaces all ¬ß7 with ¬ß8. \n"
"* ¬ß9 applies ¬ß10, ¬ß11 and (backwards) ¬ß12.\n"
"* ¬ß13 performs the replacements in the assumption ¬ß14, not in the goal. \n"
"* ¬ß15: If ¬ß16 has arguments, e.g. ¬ß17 in \n"
"¬ß18 \n"
"  or in \n"
"¬ß19, \n"
"  ¬ß20 searches the goal from left to right for a matching expression and "
"then replaces *all* occurrences *of the first* expression that it finds.\n"
"With ¬ß21, you can replace all occurrences of the ¬ß22nd expression that is "
"found instead. \n"
"\n"
"| before | Tactic | after | \n"
"|:----------------- |:-------------- |:----------------- |\n"
"| ¬ß23 | ¬ß24 | ¬ß25 | \n"
"|    | ¬ß26 | ¬ß27 | "

#. ¬ß0: `revert h`
