#. ¬ß3: `revert h`
#. ¬ß4: `contrapose`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 changes a proof goal of the form ¬ß1 to ¬ß2, thereby\n"
"initiating a proof by contraposition.\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"The tactic ¬ß3 can be useful for writing an assumption as an implication "
"premise\n"
"before you use ¬ß4."
msgstr ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 changes a goal of the form ¬ß1 to ¬ß2, thereby initiating a "
"proof by contraposition. \n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relations\n"
"\n"
" The tactic ¬ß3 can be used to write an assumption as an implication premise "
"before invoking ¬ß4."

#. ¬ß0: `contradiction`
