#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 concludes the proof if it finds a contradiction in the "
"assumptions.\n"
"Such a contradiction can look like this, for example:\n"
"\n"
"* ¬ß1\n"
"* ¬ß2 and ¬ß3\n"
"* ¬ß4\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"Normally, ¬ß5 is used to conclude a proof by contradiction\n"
"that was opened with ¬ß6."
msgstr ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 concludes the proof if it finds a contradiction among the "
"assumptions. Such a contradiction could take any of the following forms, to "
"give just a few examples: \n"
"\n"
"* ¬ß1 \n"
"* ¬ß2 and ¬ß3 \n"
"* ¬ß4 \n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relations\n"
"\n"
"The tactic ¬ß5 is commonly used to conclude a proof by contradiction that was "
"initiated with ¬ß6."

#. ¬ß0: `by_contra h`
