#. ¬ß2: `by_contra h`
#. ¬ß3: `(h : ¬¨ P)`
#. ¬ß4: `False`
#. ¬ß5: `contradiction`
#. ¬ß6: `A ‚Üí B`
#. ¬ß7: `contrapose`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 initiates a proof by contradiction.\n"
"If ¬ß1 is your current proof goal, ¬ß2 generates a new assumption ¬ß3\n"
"and sets the proof goal to ¬ß4.\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"* At the end of a proof by contradiction, there is usually ¬ß5:\n"
"this tactic closes the proof when it finds two obviously contradictory "
"assumptions.\n"
"* If the proof goal is of the form ¬ß6, you can use ¬ß7\n"
"to start a proof by contraposition."
msgstr ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 initiates a proof by contradiction. \n"
"If your current goal is ¬ß1, ¬ß2 will generate a new assumption ¬ß3 and change "
"the goal to ¬ß4. \n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relations \n"
"* A proof by contradiction usually ends with ¬ß5, the tactic that can "
"conclude ¬ß4 from contradictory assumptions.\n"
"* Given a goal of the form ¬ß6, you can start a proof by contraposition with "
"¬ß7."

#. ¬ß0: `intro`
