#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 is used for   proof goals of the form ¬ß1 or ¬ß2.\n"
"\n"
"If your proof goal is ¬ß3, ¬ß4 gives you the assumption ¬ß5, and you then have "
"to prove ¬ß6.\n"
"If your proof goal is ¬ß7, ¬ß8 gices you an arbitrary ¬ß9 and you have to prove "
"¬ß10.\n"
"\n"
"| before | tactic       | after                     |\n"
"|:------------ |:------------ |:---------------------------- |\n"
"| ¬ß11    | ¬ß12    | ¬ß13, ¬ß14               |\n"
"| ¬ß15  | ¬ß16 | ¬ß17, ¬ß18, ¬ß19 |\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"The tactic ¬ß20 does the exact opposite of ¬ß21."
msgstr ""
"Tactic ¬ß0 is used for goals of form ¬ß1 or ¬ß2. \n"
"\n"
"If your goal is ¬ß3, then you can use ¬ß4 to introduce the assumption ¬ß5, and "
"are left to prove ¬ß6. \n"
"If your goal ¬ß7, you can use ¬ß8 to pick an arbitrary ¬ß9, and are left to "
"prove ¬ß10.\n"
"\n"
"| before | tactic | after | \n"
"|:------------ |:------------ |:---------------------------- |\n"
"| ¬ß11 | ¬ß12 | ¬ß13, ¬ß14 | \n"
"| ¬ß15 | ¬ß16 | ¬ß17, ¬ß18, ¬ß19 |\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relations\n"
"\n"
"The tactic ¬ß20 does the exact opposite of ¬ß21."

#. ¬ß0: `induction n`
