#. ¬ß13: `zero_eq`
#. ¬ß14: `Nat.succ_eq_add_one`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 performs an inductive proof over ¬ß1.\n"
"With ¬ß2, you can specify names for the induction variable (here: ¬ß3)\n"
"and the induction assumption (here: ¬ß4).\n"
"The tactic thus replaces the original proof goal with two new proof goals:\n"
"* an induction start, in which ¬ß5 is set, and\n"
"* an induction step, in which the induction assumption ¬ß6 is available to "
"you.\n"
"\n"
"## Modifications in this game\n"
"\n"
"Outside of this game, ¬ß7 is called ¬ß8,\n"
"¬ß9 is initially written as ¬ß10 and ¬ß11 as ¬ß12.\n"
"These terms are identical in definition, but occasionally need to be "
"explicitly rewritten with\n"
"¬ß13 and ¬ß14."
msgstr ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 starts an inductive proof using ¬ß1. \n"
"With ¬ß2, you can specify names for the induction variable (here: ¬ß3) and the "
"inductive hypothesis (here: ¬ß4). \n"
"The tactic thus replaces the original goal with two new goals: \n"
"* the base case, in which we set ¬ß5\n"
"* the induction step, in which the inductive hypothesis ¬ß6 is available to "
"you. \n"
"\n"
"## Modifications in this game \n"
"\n"
"Outside of this game, ¬ß7 is called ¬ß8, ¬ß9 is written as ¬ß10 and ¬ß11 as ¬ß12. "
"These terms are identical by definition, but occasionally need to be "
"explicitly rewritten with ¬ß13 and ¬ß14."

#. ¬ß0: `tauto`
#. ¬ß1: `generalize`
#. ¬ß2: `tauto`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
