#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The ¬ß0 tactic breaks down an assumption into its individual parts.\n"
"\n"
"| before       | tactic                 | "
"after                                   |\n"
"|:------------------ |:--------------------- - "
"|:------------------------------------------ |\n"
"| ¬ß1        | ¬ß2 | ¬ß3 and ¬ß4                      |\n"
"| ¬ß5        | ¬ß6 | ¬ß7 and ¬ß8              |\n"
"| ¬ß9   | ¬ß10      | ¬ß11                                    |\n"
"| ¬ß12 | ¬ß13  | ¬ß14 and ¬ß15                     |\n"
"| ¬ß16        | ¬ß17   | a target with ¬ß18, a target with ¬ß19 |\n"
"\n"
"Type the brackets in the first four examples as ¬ß20 or ¬ß21.\n"
"Here, ¬ß22 is the *anonymous constructor*.\n"
"You can think of it as similar to the tuple notation in\n"
"‚Äúan abelian group is a tuple ¬ß23 such that ...‚ÄĚ."
msgstr ""
"The tactic ¬ß0 splits an assumption into its constituent parts. \n"
"\n"
"| before | tactic | after | \n"
"|:------------------ |:---------------------- "
"|:------------------------------------------ | \n"
"| ¬ß1 | ¬ß2 | ¬ß3 and ¬ß4 | \n"
"| ¬ß5 | ¬ß6 | ¬ß7 and ¬ß8 | \n"
"| ¬ß9 | ¬ß10 | ¬ß11 |\n"
"| ¬ß12 | ¬ß13 | ¬ß14 and ¬ß15 | \n"
"| ¬ß16 | ¬ß17 | one goal with ¬ß18, one goal with ¬ß19 | \n"
"\n"
"You can write the angle brackets in the first four examples as ¬ß20 and ¬ß21, "
"respectively. The expression ¬ß22 is the *anonymous constructor*.\n"
"You can think of it as similar to the tuple notation in ‚Äúan Abelian group is "
"a tuple ¬ß23 such that ‚Ä¶‚ÄĚ."

#. ¬ß0: `assumption`
