"The tactic ¬ß0 can prove equalities of expressions containing the operations "
"¬ß1 in semi-rings, in particular in ‚Ąē, ‚Ą§, ‚Ąö, ‚ĄĚ, ‚Ä¶ It works particularly well "
"in commutative rings."

#. ¬ß0: `push_neg`
#. ¬ß1: `¬¨‚ąÄ x, P x`
