#. ¬ß9: `not_forall`
#. ¬ß10: `not_exists`
#. ¬ß11: `rw`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"The ¬ß0 tactic pushes negation past quantifiers:\n"
"\n"
"| before       | after      |\n"
"|:------------ |:-------------|\n"
"| ¬ß1  | ¬ß2  |\n"
"| ¬ß3  | ¬ß4  |\n"
"\n"
"In nested expressions, it pushes the negation ¬ß5 as far to the right as "
"possible.\n"
"For example, the proof goal\n"
"¬ß6\n"
"with ¬ß7\n"
"¬ß8\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"The two lemmas ¬ß9 and ¬ß10 can be applied individually with ¬ß11."
msgstr ""
