#.   ```
#. ¬ß10: `rw [h.symm]`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With ¬ß0 (for ‚Äúsymmetry‚ÄĚ), you swap the sides of an equation (¬ß1) or "
"equivalence (¬ß2) in the proof target.\n"
"\n"
"## Variants\n"
"* ¬ß3 operates on the assumption ¬ß4 instead of the proof target\n"
"* ¬ß5 is the result of ¬ß6 and can be used like ¬ß7\n"
"\n"
"Each of the following three tactics or tactic sequences therefore has the "
"same effect:\n"
"* ¬ß8\n"
"* ¬ß9\n"
"* ¬ß10"
msgstr ""
"With ¬ß0 (for \"symmetry\"), you swap the sides of an equation (¬ß1) or "
"equivalence (¬ß2) in the goal.\n"
"\n"
"## Variants \n"
"* ¬ß3 operates on the assumption ¬ß4 instead of the goal \n"
"* ¬ß5 is the result of ¬ß6 and can be used like ¬ß7 \n"
"\n"
"So each of the following three tactics or tactic sequences has the same "
"effect: \n"
"* ¬ß8 \n"
"* ¬ß9 \n"
"* ¬ß10"

#. ¬ß0: `apply`
#. ¬ß1: `hAB : A ‚Üí B`
#. ¬ß2: `‚äĘ B`
#. ¬ß3: `apply hAB`
#. ¬ß4: `‚äĘ A`
#. ¬ß5: `h : A `
#. ¬ß6: `apply hAB at h`
#. ¬ß7: `h : B`
#. ¬ß8: `hAB`
#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With ¬ß0, you apply an implication ¬ß1:\n"
"\n"
"| before | tactic           | after |\n"
"|:------------ |:---------------- |:-------- |\n"
"| ¬ß2        | ¬ß3      | ¬ß4    |\n"
"| ¬ß5     | ¬ß6 | ¬ß7  |\n"
"\n"
"In both cases, the implication ¬ß8 can either be\n"
"given as an assumption or be an already known lemma."
msgstr ""
"With this tactic, you can ¬ß0 an implication ¬ß1: \n"
"\n"
"| before | tactic | after | \n"
"|:------------ |:---------------- |:-------- |\n"
"| ¬ß2 | ¬ß3 | ¬ß4 | \n"
"| ¬ß5 | ¬ß6 | ¬ß7 | \n"
"\n"
"In either case, the implication ¬ß8 may either be a given assumption or a "
"known lemma."

#. ¬ß0: `if ‚Ä¶ then ‚Ä¶ else`
#. ¬ß1: `fun x ‚Ü¶ if 0 ‚Č§ x then x else -x`
#. ¬ß2: `h : A`
#. ¬ß3: `rw [if_pos h]`
#. ¬ß4: `if A then B else C`
#. ¬ß5: `B`
#. ¬ß6: `h : ¬¨ A`
#. ¬ß7: `rw [if_neg h]`
#. ¬ß8: `if A then B else C`
