#: Game.Doc.Tactic
msgid ""
"With ¬ß0, you can define mappings with two branches of definition.\n"
"\n"
"For example, ¬ß1 defines the absolute value function.\n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relatives\n"
"\n"
"* If you have ¬ß2 as an assumption, you can use\n"
"¬ß3 to reduce the expression ¬ß4 to ¬ß5.\n"
"* If you have ¬ß6 as an assumption, you can use\n"
"¬ß7 to reduce the expression ¬ß8 to ¬ß9."
msgstr ""
"With ¬ß0, you can define a map piecewise. \n"
"\n"
"For example, ¬ß1 defines the absolute value function. \n"
"\n"
"## Friends and relations \n"
"\n"
"* If you have ¬ß2 as an assumption, you can use ¬ß3 to reduce the expression "
"¬ß4 to ¬ß5. \n"
"* If you have ¬ß6 as an assumption, you can use ¬ß7 to reduce the expression "
"¬ß8 to ¬ß9 in the same way."

#. ¬ß0: `generalize`
#. ¬ß1: `generalize h : a = b`
#. ¬ß2: `a`
#. ¬ß3: `b`
#. ¬ß4: `h : a = b`
#. ¬ß5: ```
