"\n"
"**Cantor**: Magic isn't for everyone. Have a good journey!"

#. ¬ß0: `‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚Ąē`
#: Game.Levels.Cantor.L11_SequenceUncountable
msgid "Intro Cantor L11: Show that set of mapping ¬ß0 is uncountable"
msgstr ""
"**Cantor**:  Easier? Who said easier?  But certainly more elegant! \n"
"\n"
"He does three backflips and then comes back with another piece of paper for "
"you.\n"
"\n"
"**Cantor**: Look! Now you can use the same argument to show that the set of "
"sequences of natural numbers, i.e. the set of maps ¬ß0, is uncountable! \n"
"\n"
"And then in a whisper: \n"
"\n"
"**Cantor**: There are uncountably many seats in this tent!"

#. ¬ß0: `n ‚Ü¶ n + 1`
#. ¬ß1: `succ`
#: Game.Levels.Cantor.L11_SequenceUncountable
msgid "The name of mapping ¬ß0 is ¬ß1"
msgstr ""
"**You**: What was the name of the map ¬ß0 again? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: ¬ß1"

#: Game.Levels.Ciao
msgid "Ciao"
msgstr "Ciao"

#: Game.Levels.Ciao
msgid "Intro Ciao"
msgstr ""
"**You**: It is possible that we've now visited *all* the planets in this "
"corner of the Leaniverse? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Looks like it.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: So what do we do now? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble:** No idea. \n"
"\n"
"After a while ‚Ä¶\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble:** Hey, look, we've received a message."

#: Game.Levels.Ciao.L01
msgid "Conclusion Cia L01"
msgstr ""
"**You**: That wasn't so difficult ‚Ä¶ I wonder who sent it? And why? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: It was definitely a message from Ritha ‚Ä¶ Scribble gazes into "
"the distance. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: I think she wanted to encourage us to travel further.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: But where to? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Oh, look, another message: \n"
"\n"
"*Dear Earthlings,* \n"
"\n"
"*It was a pleasure to meet you! We are truly sorry that you have strayed "
"into our Leaniverse and cannot find your way home. But we have some good "
"news: you are not the only ones! \n"
"Just fly on to the planet Zulip, where you will find many other Earthlings "
"who have strayed into the Leaniverse. \n"
"Zulip is large.  You will surely find a place to stay and feel comfortable "
"there. Here are the coordinates:*\n"
"\n"
"[248-4804-180 | 844-1001-553](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/"
"channel/113489-new-members/)\n"
"\n"
"*With our sincerest regards* \n"
"\n"
"*‚Äď Your Formalosophers* \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Well then ‚Äď let's go! \n"
"\n"
"[Technical note: When you follow the coordinates, the spaceship will "
"accelerate to faster-than-light speed and you will temporarily lose contact "
"with the server. But that's okay. You will arrive safely on Zulip.]"

#: Game.Levels.Epo
msgid "Epo"
msgstr "Epo"

#: Game.Levels.Epo
msgid "Intro Epo"
msgstr ""
"The planet you are now approaching has two buildings: a narrow skyscraper "
"and a second, wider building with slightly fewer floors. The buildings are "
"connected by a strange system of tubes. At the top of the skyscraper, you "
"can see a landing pad. You head for it.\n"
"\n"
"As you disembark, a formalosopher comes running towards you. He waves his "
"arms wildly. \n"
"\n"
"**Porter**: No, no, you're expected down there. He lowers his arms.\n"
"\n"
"**Porter**: Well, never mind. Good afternoon, first of all! I'm just one of "
"the porters. You are expected by a large delegation, but over there, in the "
"office building, of course. These here are just our sleeping quarters. Come "
"on, I'll take you over. It won't take long.\n"
"\n"
"He leads you down one floor and asks Robo and you to get into two single-"
"seat ‚Äútransport capsules‚ÄĚ.\n"
"\n"
"**Porter**: We'll just slide over in these capsules. Hope you enjoy it.  We "
"do have some collisions from time to time, but right now the coast is clear. "
"Everyone else is already over on the other side, waiting for you!"

#. ¬ß0: `Surjective f`
#. ¬ß1: `‚ąÄ y, (‚ąÉ x, f x = y)`
#. ¬ß2: `unfold Surjective`
#: Game.Levels.Epo.L01_Surjective
msgid "Confirm that ¬ß0 is defined as ¬ß1 via ¬ß2"
msgstr ""
"**You**: Am I right in assuming that the definition of ¬ß0 is ¬ß1? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: I think so. You could peek with ¬ß2. But you don't have to."

#: Game.Levels.Epo.L01_Surjective
msgid "Intro Epo L01"
msgstr ""
"The journey is indeed short and fun. And you indeed receive a grand "
"welcome. \n"
"Once the initial excitement has subsided, you are again confronted with some "
"questions."

#. ¬ß0: `‚Ąē ‚Üí A ‚Üí B`
#. ¬ß1: `‚Ąē ‚Üí (A ‚Üí B)`
#. ¬ß2: `‚Ąē`
#. ¬ß3: `A ‚Üí B`
#: Game.Levels.Epo.L02_CurrySurjective
msgid ""
"Explaination of ¬ß0: it can be read as ¬ß1, a mapping of ¬ß2 into the set ¬ß3"
msgstr ""
"**You**: ¬ß0 ‚Ä¶ how do I read these two arrows in a row? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: You read it as ¬ß1 ‚Äď a map from the natural numbers ¬ß2 into the "
"set ¬ß3 of maps from A to B. I guess this will also become clear as you "
"continue reading what you are supposed to show here."

#. ¬ß0: `rw [ne_comm]`
#. ¬ß1: `simp [ne_comm]`
#: Game.Levels.Epo.L02_CurrySurjective
msgid "The number of quantors does not allow for ¬ß0. Try ¬ß1"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: ¬ß0 doesn't work here because of all the quantifiers. Try ¬ß1 "
"instead."

#. ¬ß0: `constructor`
#. ¬ß1: `unfold Surjective`
#. ¬ß2: `push_neg`
#: Game.Levels.Epo.L02_CurrySurjective
msgid "Try ¬ß0 | ¬ß1, ¬ß2"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: You could start with ¬ß0, or you could start with ¬ß1 and then "
"try ¬ß2."

#. ¬ß0: `ne_comm`
#. ¬ß1: `ne_comm`
#. ¬ß2: `a ‚Č† b ‚ÜĒ b ‚Č† a`
#: Game.Levels.Epo.L02_CurrySurjective
msgid "Try ¬ß0. ¬ß1 says that ¬ß2"
msgstr "**Scribble**: Perhaps ¬ß0 would be helpful here? It says ¬ß2."

#. ¬ß0: `g`
#. ¬ß1: `f`
#. ¬ß2: `f`
#. ¬ß3: `g`
#. ¬ß4: `Function.RightInverse`
#. ¬ß5: `Function.RightInverse`
#. ¬ß6: `RightInverse`
#. ¬ß7: `RightInverse`
#: Game.Levels.Epo.L03_LeftInverse
msgid ""
"Goal says that ¬ß0 is right inverse of ¬ß1 iff ¬ß2 is left inverse of ¬ß3.\n"
"Try ¬ß4. It has to be written as ¬ß5 instead of ¬ß6\n"
"because ¬ß7 is ambigous in Leanic."
msgstr ""
"**You**: I guess this is supposed to say that ¬ß0 is a right inverse of ¬ß1 if "
"and only if ¬ß2 is a left inverse of ¬ß3.\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Exactly. But if I'm not mistaken, this is more of a definition "
"than a theorem ‚Äď ¬ß4 is simply defined in this way. And unfortunately, you "
"actually have to write ¬ß5 instead of just ¬ß6, because ¬ß7 is ambiguous in "
"Leanish."

#: Game.Levels.Epo.L04_RightInverse
msgid "Look through definitions"
msgstr ""
"**You**: So now I have to work my way through the definitions?\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Looks like it."

#. ¬ß0: `apply congr_fun at h`
#. ¬ß1: `rw [‚Üź comp_apply (f:= f)]`
#. ¬ß2: `rw [‚Üź comp_apply]`
#. ¬ß3: `(f:=f)`
#. ¬ß4: `f`
