"\n"
"¬ß0"

#. ¬ß0: `(h : A ‚ąß B)`
#. ¬ß1: `h.left`
#. ¬ß2: `h.right`
#. ¬ß3: `(h : A ‚ÜĒ B)`
#. ¬ß4: `h.mp`
#. ¬ß5: `h.mpr`
#. ¬ß6: `h.mp`
#. ¬ß7: `A ‚Üí B`
#. ¬ß8: `mp`
#. ¬ß9: `mp`
#. ¬ß10: `mpr`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L06_Iff
msgid ""
"Conclusion Implis L06: Explain that analogous to ¬ß0 with ¬ß1 and ¬ß2,\n"
"¬ß3 has ¬ß4 and ¬ß5. ¬ß6 can be understood as ¬ß7. It is ¬ß8 as ¬ß9\n"
