"**You**: ¬ß0, they're all equivalent‚Ä¶ \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Yes, but you have to help him rewrite the equivalences. With "
"¬ß1, you can replace ¬ß2 with ¬ß3."

#. ¬ß0: `‚Üź`
#. ¬ß1: `\\l`
#. ¬ß2: `rw [‚Üź h‚āď]`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L08_Rw
msgid ""
"To rewrite into the other direction you can use ¬ß0 (¬ß1) infront of the name. "
"Try ¬ß2"
msgstr ""
"**You**: And what if I want to rewrite it in the other direction? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Then you put a ¬ß0 (¬ß1, i.e. lowercase \"L\") in front of the "
"name, as in ¬ß2."

#: Game.Levels.Implis.L09_Trans
msgid "Conclusion Implis L09"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: So, was that better? \n"
"\n"
"**You**: Don't know. Anyway, we can carry on."

#. ¬ß0: `rw`
#. ¬ß1: `trans`
#. ¬ß2: $B \\iff A \\iff D \\iff C$
#. ¬ß3: `trans A`
#. ¬ß4: `B \\iff A`
#. ¬ß5: `trans D`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L09_Trans
msgid ""
"Intro Implis L09: Instead of ¬ß0 use ¬ß1 here.\n"
"With it you can solve ¬ß2 step-by-step by using\n"
"¬ß3 to introduce the intermediate step ¬ß4 and then\n"
"perfrom The next step with ¬ß5"
msgstr ""
"**You**: Somehow, all these ¬ß0s feel a bit unintuitive. Can't we argue in a "
"way that is slightly more straightforward?\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Maybe you'd prefer ¬ß1? With ¬ß1, you can work through your "
