msgstr ""
"**Head of Operations**: This is for my rather limited colleague again. \n"
"I don't think he likes ¬ß0 either. Can you manage without?"

#. ¬ß0: `apply`
#. ¬ß1: `¬ę{h}¬Ľ`
#. ¬ß2: `rw [‚Üź ¬ę{h}¬Ľ]`
#. ¬ß3: `¬ę{A}¬Ľ ‚Üí ¬ę{B}¬Ľ`
#. ¬ß4: `¬ę{h}¬Ľ`
#. ¬ß5: `¬ę{h}¬Ľ.mp`
#. ¬ß6: `apply (¬ę{h}¬Ľ.mp) at ‚Ä¶`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L10_Iff
msgid ""
"We know that ¬ß0 can be used on implications. Intuitively, for equivalence "
"¬ß1\n"
"one could use ¬ß2. The direction ¬ß3 of ¬ß4 is denoted by ¬ß5.\n"
"Try ¬ß6"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: Well, you could ¬ß0 an implication ‚Ä¶ \n"
"\n"
"**You**: I know! But ¬ß1 is not an implication, it's an equivalence. So I'd "
"want to say something like ¬ß2. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: The direction ¬ß3 of ¬ß4 is called ¬ß5. You can apply it with ¬ß6."

#: Game.Levels.Implis.L11_Iff
msgid "Conclusion Implis L11"
msgstr "**Head of Operations**: Perfect, that should do it!"

#. ¬ß0: `intro`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L11_Iff
msgid "Exactly, try ¬ß0"
msgstr "**Scribble**: Exactly, that was ¬ß0."

#: Game.Levels.Implis.L11_Iff
msgid "Goal is in assumptions"
msgstr "**You**: Ah, and now our goal is among the assumptions."

#. ¬ß0: `rw [¬ę{h}¬Ľ]`
