#. ¬ß2: `obtain ‚ü®mp, mpr‚ü© := ¬ę{h}¬Ľ`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L11_Iff
msgid "Instead of ¬ß0 and ¬ß1 try ¬ß2"
msgstr ""
"**You**: Well, I know ¬ß0 and ¬ß1, but we wanted to avoid those this time. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: What you could do is split the assumption into two parts with "
"¬ß2."

#. ¬ß0: `rw`
#. ¬ß1: `apply`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L11_Iff
msgid "Intro Implis L11: Prove without using ¬ß0 or ¬ß1"
msgstr ""
"**Head of Operations**: Ah, the next page is also from this colleague. But "
"there's another note on it. We already had a proof of this, but he didn't "
"like it. He wanted proof that uses neither ¬ß0 nor ¬ß1! \n"
"\n"
"He takes a deep breath and sighs.\n"
"\n"
"**Head of Operations**: I'm pretty sure he's just playing dumb. But never "
"mind.  Do you think you could do it?"

#: Game.Levels.Implis.L11_Iff
msgid "Start with implication"
msgstr "**You**: Hmm ‚Ä¶ I guess I could start with the implication."

#: Game.Levels.Implis.L12_ByCases
msgid "Conclusion Implis L12"
msgstr "The Head of Operations nods in agreement."

#. ¬ß0: `A`
#. ¬ß1: `¬¨A`
#. ¬ß2: `by_cases h : A`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L12_ByCases
msgid "Either ¬ß0 or ¬ß1 is true. Try ¬ß2"
msgstr ""
"**You**: Well, one of the two statements ¬ß0 or ¬ß1 will be true. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Sounds like a classic case distinction! Try ¬ß2."

#: Game.Levels.Implis.L12_ByCases
msgid "Intro Implis L12"
msgstr ""
"The next sheet of paper gives the Head of Operations pause. \n"
"\n"
"**Head of Operations**: To be honest, I have no idea where this came from. \n"
"It's not mine. But it looks interesting somehow."

#. ¬ß0: `A`
#. ¬ß1: `A`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L12_ByCases
msgid ""
"Proof consists now of two parts. First assumes that ¬ß0 is true. Second "
"assumes that ¬ß1\n"
"is false"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: You see, now the proof has two parts. In the first part, you "
"assume that ¬ß0 is true. In the second part, you assume that ¬ß1 is false."

#. ¬ß0: `not_not`
#. ¬ß1: `‚ÜĒ`
#. ¬ß2: `=`
#. ¬ß3: `rw`
#. ¬ß4: `rw [not_not]`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L13_Rw
msgid ""
"A lemma like ¬ß0 that contains ¬ß1 or ¬ß2 in its statements can also be used "
