msgstr ""
"**You**: Are we done already ‚Ä¶? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Yes, ¬ß0 always includes a ¬ß1, and that worked here."

#. ¬ß0: `apply`
#. ¬ß1: ```
#. lemma not_not (A : Prop) : ¬¨¬¨A ‚ÜĒ A
#. ```
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L13_Rw
msgid ""
"Intro Implis L13: Do not use ¬ß0. Try it with\n"
"¬ß1"
msgstr ""
"**Head of Operations**: Something else for my colleague ‚Ä¶and he again asked "
"for a proof without ¬ß0. I had already made myself a little note here. There "
"is this lemma: \n"
"\n"
"¬ß1\n"
"\n"
"**Head of Operations**: Do you think that's useful here?"

#. ¬ß0: `¬¨¬¨`
#. ¬ß1: `rw`
#. ¬ß2: `¬¨¬¨C`
#. ¬ß3: `¬¨¬¨B`
#: Game.Levels.Implis.L13_Rw
msgid ""
"Only two of three ¬ß0 are rewritten. ¬ß1 only rewrites only first found "
"occurance i.e. ¬ß2.\n"
"As ¬ß3 is considered to be something 'different' the lemma has to be applied "
