"Applying ¬ß0 onto ¬ß1 is usually badly readable. Try ¬ß2 directly afterwards"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: Actually, applying ¬ß0 to ¬ß1 always results in a bit of chaos. "
"It's best to always follow up with ¬ß2, then things becomes readable again."

#: Game.Levels.Prado.L09_ExistsUnique
msgid "Intro Prado L09"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**:  It's not actually that difficult. Here, take a look at this "
"problem."

