"\n"
"**You**: We have a letter for your queen. Could you take us to her? \n"
"\n"
"**All formalosophers** *(in unison)*: We're all here! \n"
"\n"
"**You**: Okay. So which one of you is the queen? \n"
"\n"
"An awkward silence ensues. Everyone shrugs their shoulders.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: Do you have a queen? \n"
"\n"
"**All** *(in unison)*: Yes, yes. We have a queen, we have a queen. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble** *(to you)*: Let me summarise. There is a queen, but no one "
"knows who she is ‚Ä¶ \n"
"\n"
"**You**: Isn't that a contradiction?\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Seriously? You as a mathematician call that a contradiction? \n"
"It's not a contradiction. It's simply a ‚Äúpure statement of existence‚ÄĚ. \n"
"\n"
"Now you're unsure how serious *he* is. \n"
"\n"
"**You**: In that case, I suggest we simply hand the parcel over to *all* the "
"residents. \n"
"Then, in particular, we will have handed it over to the queen.\n"
"\n"
"**You** *(to the crowd)*: We have brought you a package from Implis. \n"
"Here, this is for you. \n"
"\n"
"Scribble throws it into the crowd, and the formalosophers tear it open. \n"
"It turns out there is only a single piece of paper inside. \n"
"After a few minutes, it is back with you. \n"
"And the formalosophers are all looking curiously at you, to see how you will "
"handle it."

#: Game.Levels.Quantus
