#. ¬ß1: `‚ÜĒ`
#. ¬ß2: `rw`
#: Game.Levels.Saturn.L01_Rewrite_equality
msgid "Explain that ¬ß0 and ¬ß1 with ¬ß2 can be used as in Implis"
msgstr ""
"**You**: I feel like I've seen this before. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Yes! It looks very similar to a problem we already solved on "
"*Implis*. Except that this one has equalities of numbers instead of if-then "
"statements! But that doesn't really make any difference. You can treat ¬ß0 "
"and ¬ß1 practically the same as ¬ß2."

#: Game.Levels.Saturn.L01_Rewrite_equality
msgid "Intro Saturn L01"
msgstr "Suddenly, you receive a radio message."

