msgid "Explain misfit of ¬ß0. Try ¬ß1 via ¬ß2"
msgstr ""
"**You**:  Is this from some Annoying Algebra Anonymous club? Clearly, one "
"just needs to rearrange the terms bit. Perhaps we should answer with ¬ß0?\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: No, in this universe, the equation is naturally called ¬ß1, "
"simply because formula contains first a ‚Äú+‚ÄĚ and then a ‚Äú^2‚ÄĚ. So you could "
"use ¬ß2. Then the left side will look exactly like the right side, and you're "
"done."

#: Game.Levels.Saturn.L02_Ring_add_pow_two
msgid "Intro Saturn L02"
msgstr "The next radio message looks a little different."

#: Game.Levels.Saturn.L03_mul_comm
msgid "Conclusion Saturn L03"
msgstr "Another ūüĎć."

