msgstr "**Scribble**: Why not start with ¬ß0?"

#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L04_ByContra
msgid "Use proof by contradiction"
msgstr "**Scribble**: Here, again, I would try a proof by introduction."

#. ¬ß0: `suffices g : ¬¨ A`
#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L04_ByContra
msgid "¬ß0 would be a good option"
msgstr "**Scribble**: ¬ß0 strikes me as a good move."

#. ¬ß0: `contrapose`
#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L05_Contrapose
msgid "Apply contraposition lemma simply by ¬ß0"
msgstr ""
"**You**: And now I can apply this contraposition thingy? What was it called "
"again? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Actually, you can just write ¬ß0."

#. ¬ß0: `even_square`
#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L05_Contrapose
msgid "Apply lemma ¬ß0"
msgstr ""
"**You**: That's looking good. Now I can actually apply the lemma ¬ß0 from "
"before!"

#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L05_Contrapose
msgid "Conclusion Spinoza L05"
msgstr "**Benedictus**: Excellent! I think you're well prepared now."

#. ¬ß0: `by_contra`
#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L05_Contrapose
msgid "Intro Spinoza L05. prove without ¬ß0"
msgstr ""
"**Benedictus**: Right, here's the question I promised. Try to come up with a "
"*direct* proof, without ¬ß0."

#. ¬ß0: `even_square`
#. ¬ß1: `Odd (n^2) ‚Üí Odd n`
#. ¬ß2: `Even n ‚Üí Even (n^2)`
#. ¬ß3: `‚Üí`
#. ¬ß4: `revert`
#. ¬ß5: `revert ¬ę{h}¬Ľ`
#. ¬ß6: `¬ę{h}¬Ľ`
