"contraposition, that's equivalent to ¬ß2.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: Right. Let's take some elementary statement and show it in the most "
"convoluted way possible ‚Ä¶ But wait, there's no ¬ß3 here. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Remember ¬ß4. With ¬ß5, you can push the assumption ¬ß6 into the "
"goal."

#. ¬ß0: `not_odd_iff_even`
#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L05_Contrapose
msgid "¬ß0 might help here"
msgstr "**Scribble**: Perhaps ¬ß0 would be useful now?"

#. ¬ß0: `suffices d : ¬¨ Odd (n ^ 2)`
#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L06_Summary
msgid "Conclude with ¬ß0"
msgstr "**Scribble**: That is: ¬ß0."

#. ¬ß0: `have`
#. ¬ß1: `suffices`
#. ¬ß2: `by_contra`
#. ¬ß3: `contradiction`
#. ¬ß4: `contrapose`
#. ¬ß5: `revert`
#. ¬ß6: `contrapose`
