"Conclusion Spinoza L06: overview of planet's contents:\n"
"¬ß0, ¬ß1, ¬ß2, ¬ß3, ¬ß4, ¬ß5 (useful when applying\n"
"¬ß6 afterwards)."
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: Well done! Here's an overview of what Benediktus showed us. \n"
"\n"
"\n"
"| **Tactic** | **Purpose** | \n"
"|:----------------|:-------------------------------------------------------| \n"
"| ¬ß0 | Accept interim result | \n"
"| ¬ß1 | Accept interim result |\n"
"| ¬ß2 | Begin proof of contradiction | \n"
"| ¬ß3 | Conclude proof of contradiction | \n"
"| ¬ß4 | Contraposition | \n"
"| ¬ß5 | Useful for applying ¬ß6 afterwards | "

#. ¬ß0: `Odd (n ^ 2)`
#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L06_Summary
msgid "Derive contradiction for ¬ß0"
msgstr "**Scribble**: Now I would derive a contradiction with ¬ß0."

#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L06_Summary
msgid "Intro Spinoza L06"
msgstr ""
"**You**: But couldn't we have proven the last statement just as easily by "
"contradiction? \n"
"\n"
"**Benedictus**: Sure. I just thought a second proof by contradiction would "
"be boring. But you are welcome to try the problem again. Here, I'll give it "
"to you to take with you on your journey. But now make sure you get going!"

#. ¬ß0: `by_contra g`
#: Game.Levels.Spinoza.L06_Summary
msgid "This time start with ¬ß0"
msgstr ""
"Once you've managed to escape from the asteroid's gravitational field, you "
"return to the problem at hand. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Okay, so this time we'll start with ¬ß0!"

#: Game.Levels.Vieta
msgid "Intro Vieta"
msgstr ""
"Hello, is anyone here? You have landed in some shrubland. There is no one to "
"be seen far and wide. \n"
"\n"
"Suddenly, an arrow whizzes right over your head. \n"
"\n"
"**You**: Take cover!\n"
"\n"
"You throw yourself flat on the ground. You're about to crawl back to the "
"spaceship when a man emerges from behind a withered tree and waves friendly. "
"So you crawl towards him. \n"
"\n"
"**Vieta**: Don't be shy, ladies and gentlemen! My name is Vieta. Welcome! "
"Get up, the coast is clear.\n"
"\n"
"You rise cautiously, but another arrow whizzes past you. \n"
"\n"
"**You**: How do you manage to live here? \n"
"\n"
"**Vieta**: I've learned to always be in the right place at the right time. "
"Don't worry."

#: Game.Levels.Vieta
msgid "Vieta"
msgstr "Vieta"

#. ¬ß0: `‚Üí`
#: Game.Levels.Vieta.L01_FunctionNotation
msgid "Conclusion Vieta L01: explain ambiguity of ¬ß0"
msgstr ""
"**You**:  Wasn't ¬ß0 an implication a moment ago? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Yes, that's right. They use the same symbol for a map and for "
"an implication here."

#. ¬ß0: `f`
#. ¬ß1: `‚Ą§`
#. ¬ß2: `‚Ąē`
#. ¬ß3: `f n`
#. ¬ß4: $f(n)$
#. ¬ß5: `f (n)`
#: Game.Levels.Vieta.L01_FunctionNotation
msgid ""
"Explain ¬ß0 as mapping from ¬ß1 to ¬ß2:\n"
"¬ß3 is notation for ¬ß4. If you want to use brackets it has to be ¬ß5.\n"
msgstr ""
"**You**: It looks like ¬ß0 is a map from ¬ß1 to ¬ß2. \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Yes, exactly. And ¬ß3 is notation for ¬ß4. You just don't put "
