msgid ""
"Explain anonymous function ¬ß0 as mapping ¬ß1.\n"
"Only ¬ß2 the anon. function would receive a name. The goal is for\n"
"¬ß3\n"
"to show that ¬ß4.\n"
"You can try ¬ß5 or ¬ß6\n"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: Ah, that's interesting. Here, ¬ß0 is an ‚Äúanonymous function‚ÄĚ, "
"namely the map ¬ß1. \n"
"\n"
"**You**: And what is anonymous about it? \n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Well, for starters, it doesn't have a name. It only gets a "
"name through ¬ß2. \n"
"\n"
"**You**: I see.  So overall, we have the following map, right?\n"
"\n"
"¬ß3\n"
"\n"
"So I'm supposed to show ¬ß4?\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Yes.\n"
"\n"
"**You**: And how do I do that here?\n"
"\n"
"**Scribble**: Lean can see through most mapping rules, so ¬ß5 should suffice "
"here. Alternatively, you can explicitly use the definition with ¬ß6. \n"

#: Game.Levels.Vieta.L02_Function
msgid "Intro Vieta L02"
msgstr ""
"Another arrow whizzes past. Vieta calmly hands you the next piece of paper."

#. ¬ß0: `¬ę{f}¬Ľ`
#. ¬ß1: `use`
#: Game.Levels.Vieta.L03_Let
msgid "If ¬ß0 correctly defind try ¬ß1"
msgstr ""
"**Scribble**: If you have defined ¬ß0 correctly, you can now ¬ß1 it, and the "
"resulting inequality should be straightforward."

#: Game.Levels.Vieta.L03_Let
msgid "Intro Vieta L03"
msgstr "Another arrow. And another problem."

